{
    "name": "Basque-Style Codfish Stew",
    "instructions": "1. Soak salted codfish in about 2 quarts of water, changing the water three times over the course of 8 hours. Drain, then cut codfish into bite-sized pieces.\n\n2. Layer 1/2 of each ingredient in a pot in the following order: potatoes, codfish, onions, hard-boiled eggs, capers, garlic, olives, roasted red peppers, and raisins.\n\n3. Place bay leaf on raisins, then pour 1/2 of the tomato sauce and 1/2 of the olive oil over top. Repeat layers in the same order, skipping bay leaf.\n\n4. Pour water and white wine over top; do not stir.\n\n5. Cover and bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.",
    "simpleInstructions": "1. Soak codfish and cut into pieces.\n\n2. Layer ingredients in a pot.\n\n3. Pour liquids over and simmer until tender.",
